      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WESTAR LEO (5) was game in defeat when finished in the minors last start over the 450m at Shepparton, running a good 25.28 in a Restricted WIN. In form and looks the one to beat. PAW BENNETT (1) finds it hard to break through. Finished third (27.72) at this track last time making it three minors on end. Goes well out of this box with a win and three minor placings. Deserves a win and gets his chance. DYNAMITE ERIC (2) drew a squeeze box and was game in defeat when a close second, a neck from the winner Balding Sandy (27.70) at this track. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card. Hard to beat again. HAPPY DAD (4) showed plenty of dash to record a last start win. Right in the mix.",
